<subsection xml:id="subsec-opposite-of-a-vector">
    <title>Opposite of a vector</title>
    
    <p>
        The vector which has the same magnitude as that of a vector <m>\overrightarrow{AB},</m> but opposite in direction is called <m>{\color{red}\text{opposite vector of }}</m> <m>\overrightarrow{AB}</m> and is denoted by <m>-\overrightarrow{AB}.</m> 
        From <xref ref="opposite-vector-1"/>, you can observe that one vector is the negative of the other. Thus, <m>a = -(-a)</m> as shown in the first part of <xref ref="opposite-vector-1"/> and <m>\overrightarrow{AB} = -\overrightarrow{CD}</m> 
        as shown in the second part of <xref ref="opposite-vector-1"/>.
    </p>
